		<title>How To Tell If You Are in a Baby-Sitters Club Book</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/ThePassiveVoice/~3/_PzIVoTuZ2U/</link>
		<comments>http://www.thepassivevoice.com/12/2014/how-to-tell-if-you-are-in-a-baby-sitters-club-book/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Sat, 13 Dec 2014 19:20:33 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Passive Guy]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Children's Books]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.thepassivevoice.com/?p=58739</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[From The Toast: Your peer group has associate members. You have something called a Kid Kit filled with toys that you present to children with regularity, but it isn’t creepy. You hide candy in absurd places in your bedroom, but you do not have an ant problem. Each of your adventures starts with a recap [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>From The Toast:</p>
<blockquote><p>Your peer group has associate members.</p>
<p>You have something called a Kid Kit filled with toys that you present to children with regularity, but it isn’t creepy.</p>
<p>You hide candy in absurd places in your bedroom, but you do not have an ant problem.</p>
<p>Each of your adventures starts with a recap of who your friends are, what they look like, and their job in your organization.</p>
<p>You and your friends run a weird, complicated, under-the-table small business, but only one of you is “bossy.”</p>
<p>. . . .</p>
<p>You take great pleasure in listing every article of clothing you’re wearing, as well as every article of clothing each of your six closest friends are wearing.</p>
<p>Your shyest friend has a dreamy boyfriend with a southern accent. Nobody understands why, including said boyfriend.</p>
<p>You have been in literally every extracurricular activity your school has to offer, but never for longer than two weeks.</p>
<p>You find yourself oddly attracted to the supernatural and situations that could be described as mysterious. On some more memorable locations, you’ve even helped the police solve seemingly inexplicable crimes. And you’re not even in high school yet.</p>
<p>You frequently embark on cross-country and even transatlantic trips that are sponsored by your school. Your <em>middle</em> school.</p></blockquote>
<p>Link to the rest at <a href="http://the-toast.net/2014/12/09/tell-baby-sitters-club-book/"  target="_blank" rel="nofollow">The Toast</a></p>
<p>If you have no idea what The Babysitters Club is <a href="http://www.amazon.com/s/?_encoding=UTF8&amp;camp=1789&amp;creative=390957&amp;field-keywords=Baby-Sitters%20Club&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;tag=thepasvoi01-20&amp;url=search-alias%3Daps&amp;linkId=6B5PHOHNX5W5HSXO"  target="_blank" rel="nofollow">here&#8217;s a link</a><img style="border: none !important; margin: 0px !important;" src="https://ir-na.amazon-adsystem.com/e/ir?t=thepasvoi01-20&amp;l=ur2&amp;o=1" alt="" width="1" height="1" border="0" />. One of PG&#8217;s offspring was a huge fan when she was younger.</p>
